This code carry out the first quality control check on all reads to get an idea of what do next
Once you have your QC files, you will need to run FASTP to remove any adapter sequences and other poor seq info
*********************************************************************************************************************
I used this code to run fastqc:
nohup time fastqc -t 60 *.fastq -o D4993-C5-LG3-Sat_fastqc

Path: /home/yggshare/ALL_DATA/00.read_data/11.Seq2Sat/01_rawreads/D4993-C5-LG3-Sat

Next, FAstQC was performed on the output obtained from FASTP run. The following code was used to generate the final QC:
nohup time fastqc -t 75 /home/yggshare/ALL_DATA/00.read_data/11.Seq2Sat/01_rawreads/D4993-C5-LG3-Sat/D4993-C5-LG3-Sat_fastqc_fastp/*.fastq -o D4993-C5-LG3-Sat_fastqc_fastp-FASTQC &

FastQC on the raw reads from KEA and VDA paper:
nohup time fastqc -t 60 /home/yggshare/current_projects/Guaymas2020/00.raw_data/NC_State_NovaSeq/FastqFiles_NVS070B_Baker_R1/4993_5_H3_S3_R1_001.fastq.gz /home/yggshare/current_projects/Guaymas2020/00.raw_data/NC_State_NovaSeq/FastqFiles_NVS070B_Baker_R2/4993_5_H3_S3_R2_001.fastq.gz /home/yggshare/current_projects/Guaymas2020/00.raw_data/NC_State_NovaSeq/FastqFiles_NVS070B_Baker_R1/4993_5_LG_S4_R1_001.fastq.gz  /home/yggshare/current_projects/Guaymas2020/00.raw_data/NC_State_NovaSeq/FastqFiles_NVS070B_Baker_R2/4993_5_LG_S4_R2_001.fastq.gz -o 4993_5_H3_S3-4993_5_LG_S4-fastqc &

Lastly, FastQC was performed on the fastp'd KEA and VDA metagenomes
nohup time fastqc -t 40 /home/yggshare/ALL_DATA/00.read_data/11.Seq2Sat/01_rawreads/D4993-C5-LG3-Sat/4993_5_H3_S3-4993_5_LG_S4_fastqc-fastp/*.gz -o /home/yggshare/ALL_DATA/00.read_data/11.Seq2Sat/01_rawreads/D4993-C5-LG3-Sat/4993_5_H3_S3-4993_5_LG_S4-fastp-FASTQC &
